According to the Bureau of Labor&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:35.520 --> 00:04:42.480
Statistics – Americans spend twice as much&nbsp;
on jewelry, watches, books and phones today&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:49.200
as they did twenty-five years ago, new American&nbsp;
homes are almost 25% bigger today than they were&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:57.760
25 years ago, and Americans throw away five times&nbsp;
more consumer waste today than they did in 1980.
