fee” for goods entering the U.S. from China.
&nbsp;

00:16:20.640 --> 00:16:26.160
Some people have argued that if prices go up&nbsp;
due to tariffs that Americans will just start&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:26.160 --> 00:16:32.800
buying smaller quantities of higher quality goods.&nbsp;
There is no real reason to believe that however.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:39.520
Typically tariffs drive up the price of imported&nbsp;
goods – but they also allow domestic producers to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:16:39.520 --> 00:16:46.400
increase their prices – which they typically do.
Ramon Van Meer – who runs a business selling&nbsp;&nbsp;

